comments: There were a couple of places I'm not sure that the image showed properly. Two places I only saw a block of color on one side. One place I saw a block of color, then an image then another image flashed then back to the first image. Not sure if that's a problem or a trick but all the others worked as the directions described.
strategy: At one point I thought there was a pattern of the more complex objects being the ones that I'd have to remember so I focused a bit more on those for a little while. I also tried to name an object with the color then put an image in my mind of the other object. For most of it I just stared in the middle and put an image in my mind so I could refer to that image (in my mind) while I was determining the color on the wheel. The problem with that strategy is I got bored and if my mind wandered even a little I would have trouble seeing the image or storing it in my mind.
